canonical:
  title: 瀟湘八景
  author: 姜希孟
  language: lzh
  text: 遠浦歸帆咽咽汀潮上逢逢鼉鼓催湖平風熟衆帆開隱暎鏡光來縹渺鷗邊𤄃微茫烟際回群檣繫纜白沙堆江殷地中雷平沙落鴈冥路通雲漢低飛爲稻梁排空點點字千行去意在三湘沙遠平鋪雪蘆深冷着霜驚寒千陣向衡陽作勢抑還揚洞庭秋月雲物掃銀漢露華凝碧空衡湘萬里混西東暗淡有無中海角迷金暈乾端射白虹冰輪輾上駕長風冷徹碧雲宮瀟湘夜雨雲烟藏海嶠風雨滿汀洲水國蒹葭響晩秋燈前萬里愁寒聲聞竹岸遙火認漁舟五夜不眠篷底幽哀鳴三兩鷗山市晴嵐遠岫靑如䯻輕嵐白作圍茅茨何處掩柴扉空翠落霏霏野徑通林細溪橋跨岸微試敎摩詰書圖歸眞趣也應非江天暮雪頑雲垂地暗密雪挾風嚴薄暮擎寒竹枝纖擺亞落輕塩蓑重回漁棹村孤誇酒帘江樓霽景帶寒蟾倚醉喚鉤簾煙寺暮鍾樹密招提隱烟沉紫翠濃鯨音忽撼暯山容三十六聲鍾役役悲塵世悠悠望翠峯偶然深省倚孤筇暝色入蒼松漁村落照山遠㘅斜日江澄漾彩霞漁人相聚自成家籬落整還斜橋斷明秋水林高返暯鴉阿翁收網入蘆花談咲說魚蝦
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 瀟湘八景
  author: 姜希孟
  language: lzh
  text: 遠浦歸帆咽咽汀潮上。逢逢鼉鼓催。湖平風熟衆帆開。隱暎鏡光來。縹渺鷗邊𤄃。微茫烟際回。群檣繫纜白沙堆。江殷地中雷。平沙落鴈冥路通雲漢。低飛爲稻梁。排空點點字千行。去意在三湘。沙遠平鋪雪。蘆深冷着霜。驚寒千陣向衡陽。作勢抑還揚。洞庭秋月雲物掃銀漢。露華凝碧空。衡湘萬里混西東。暗淡有無中。海角迷金暈。乾端射白虹。冰輪輾上駕長風。冷徹碧雲宮。瀟湘夜雨雲烟藏海嶠。風雨滿汀洲。水國蒹葭響。晩秋燈前萬里愁。寒聲聞竹岸。遙火認漁舟。五夜不眠篷底幽。哀鳴三兩鷗。山市晴嵐遠岫靑如䯻。輕嵐白作圍。茅茨何處掩柴扉。空翠落霏霏。野徑通林細。溪橋跨岸微。試敎摩詰書圖歸。眞趣也應非。江天暮雪頑雲垂地暗。密雪挾風嚴。薄暮擎寒竹枝纖。擺亞落輕塩。蓑重回漁棹。村孤誇酒帘。江樓霽景帶寒蟾。倚醉喚鉤簾。煙寺暮鍾樹密招提隱。烟沉紫翠濃。鯨音忽撼暯山容。三十六聲鍾。役役悲塵世。悠悠望翠峯。偶然深省倚孤筇。暝色入蒼松。漁村落照山遠㘅斜日。江澄漾彩霞。漁人相聚自成家。籬落整還斜。橋斷明秋水。林高返暯鴉。阿翁收網入蘆花。談咲說魚蝦。
korean:
  title: 소상팔경
  author: 강희맹
  language: kor
  text: |-
    원포귀범(遠逋歸帆)껄떡껄떡 개포엔 조수 오르고
    둥당둥당 큰 북소리 재촉하네
    편한 호수 바람 자고 뭇 돛이 펼쳐질 제
    숨는 듯 비치는 듯 빛이 다가오네
    나풀거려 해오라기 가에 돌고
    아득히도 연기 가로 돌아오네
    뭇 돛대는 흰 모래에 닻줄 매었는데
    강물 속 흐르는 소 땅 속에 우뢰인양 은은하이
    평사낙안(平沙落雁)어둔 길은 은하수로 통했는데
    낮게 날아 도량을 구하련다
    공중에 점점이 몇 줄이 되었던고
    가는 뜻은 응당 삼상에 있으련만
    먼 모래에 눈은 평평히 깔렸고
    갈대 깊은 곳 찬 서리에 붙였도다
    놀라서 평양으로 가는 그 몇 진이
    형세 이뤄 굽었다 또 드날리네
    동정추월(洞庭秋月)은하엔 구름도 쓸어낸 듯
    이슬빛 푸른 공중에 어리었네
    형과 상은 만리 길 동서로 섞였는데
    보일락말락 그저 암담하여라
    바닷가엔 금빛이 아득하고
    하늘 끝엔 흰 무지개 빛을 쏘네
    얼음 바퀴 굴러 올라 긴 바람 날려갈 제
    찬 기운 벽운궁에 가득 차 있어라
    소상야우(瀟湘夜雨)구름 연기바다 메를 삼켜 있고
    비바람 물가에 가득하네
    물 나라 갈대는 늦가을을 울리는데
    등불 앞엔 만리의 시름이라
    차가운 소리 숲 언덕에 들려오고
    먼 불빛 어주인 줄 알게 하네
    새벽까지 잠 안 자니 뜰 아래라 고요한데
    두세 백구 슬피만 울더라
    산시청람(山市晴嵐)먼 봉우리 상투처럼 푸르렀고
    가벼운 메 기운 희게 에워쌌네
    띠집 어느 곳에 사립문이 닫혔던고
    허공에 푸른 빛은 부실부실 떨어질 듯
    들길은 숲을 꿰어 가느다란데
    시내 다리 언덕 걸쳐 조그맣네
    마힐 불러 이 경치 그려본들
    참된 그 취미 응당 표현 못하리라
    강천모설(江天暮雪)검은 구름 땅에 드리워 어둡고
    빽빽한 눈 바람 끼고 혹독하다
    황혼 찬기운 겪고선 대까지 가느다란데
    흔들리면 가벼운 소금 살살 흩노매라
    도롱이 무거워서 고깃배 돌려 오니
    마을이 외로운데 술기만을 자랑하네
    강 다락 갠 경치 찬 달빛 띠었으니
    취한 채 아이 불러 주렴 올려 걸었어라
    연사모종(煙寺暮鐘)숲이 빽빽하여 절이 숨어 있고
    내 잠기니 붉고 푸름 짙었어라
    목어 소리 홀연히 산 모양 흔드니
    서른 여섯 차례 그 종소리
    소리마다 티끌 세상 슬퍼하네
    유유히 푸른 봉을 바라보노라면
    우연히 깨친 바 있어 외론 막대 비기니
    어둠 빛은 푸른 솔로 들어갔어라
    어촌낙조(漁村落照)먼 메는 지는 해를 삼키고
    맑은 강에 채색 놀이 얼른얼른
    고기잡이 서로 모여 절로 멧집 이룩되니
    울타리는 곧다가도 비끼어라
    다리가 끊이매 가을 물이 밝고
    숲이 높아 저녁 까마귀 돌아오네
    어옹이 그물 거두어 갈꽃으로 들어가서
    고기랑 새우랑 웃으며 애기하더라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1460_030_0030&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 목어(木魚) : '
    value: 원문에는 고래[鯨]라고 하였으나, 원래는 절에 나무로 고기 형상을 만들어 단 것인데, 그것을 쳐서 소리 나게 한다.
english:
  title: Eight Views of the Xiao and Xiang Rivers
  author: Kang Hee-maeng
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Returning Sails at the Distant Wharf

    The small pier sucks and swallows as the tide rises,
    the great drum's dong-dong-dong hastens the boats.
    When the lake grows calm and the wind sleeps,
    all sails unfurl in a gathered fleet.
    Light glimmers, hides, then glimmers again as it approaches—
    wildfowl flutter at the edge of mist,
    receding into the haze.
    Mast after mast lashes its anchor to white sand,
    while the river's thunder rolls through the earth like distant lightning.

    Wild Geese Descending on Sandbank

    The dark path opens into the Milky Way,
    they fly low, seeking sustenance.
    Point by point, they write themselves across the sky in rows,
    their journey's heart surely bent toward the three rivers of Xiang.
    On distant sands, snow lies flat and level;
    in deep reeds, frost clings, cold and sharp.
    A thousand flocks in formation startle toward Hengyang,
    their shapes bending down, then rising once more.

    Autumn Moon at Dongting Lake

    Clouds sweep from the silver river;
    dew-light gathers in the blue void.
    For ten thousand li, Heng and Xiang blend east and west—
    in that dimness between being and nothingness.
    At the world's edge, golden halos shimmer,
    from heaven's zenith, a white rainbow shoots forth.
    The ice-wheel turns and ascends, riding the long wind,
    and cold pierce deep into the palace of green clouds.

    Night Rain on the Xiao and Xiang

    Clouds and mist swallow the distant sea-cliffs,
    wind and rain flood the river banks.
    In the water-kingdom, reeds cry out in late autumn;
    before the lamp, ten thousand li of sorrow.
    Cold sounds drift from the bamboo shore,
    distant fire reveals the fisherman's boat.
    Till dawn we lie sleepless beneath our canvas roof,
    while two or three white gulls keen their mournful song.

    Mountain Town in Clear Haze

    Distant peaks rise blue as a topknot,
    light mist weaves white围 around them.
    Where does the thatched cottage hide its narrow gate?
    Blue emptiness showers down like drifting dust.
    Wild paths thread through groves, thread-thin,
    creeks bridge the banks, barely wide enough.
    Though one might summon the painter's brush to capture this,
    the true essence could never be contained.

    River Sky in Evening Snow

    Dark clouds hang low, the earth grows dim,
    thick snow rides the wind in bitter waves.
    At dusk, cold pierces even the slender bamboo;
    each sway lets fall a grain of salt.
    Heavy raincoat bends the fisherman's boat homeward,
    the lonely village boasts only its tavern sign.
    From the river tower, in the cleared evening light, a cold moon lingers—
    drunken, we call for the servants to draw up the blind.

    Smoky Temple's Evening Bell

    Forests crowd so thick the monastery hides,
    smoke settles until red and green grow dense.
    The temple block suddenly stirs the mountain's face—
    thirty-six tolls of the great bell sound.
    Each note grieves the dusty world,
    while soft and long the gaze turns to green peaks.
    By chance a moment of awakening comes,
    leaning on a lonely staff as darkness enters the pines.

    Fishing Village at Sunset

    The distant mountain swallows the setting sun,
    the clear river dances with colored light.
    Fishermen gather and make a village of their own,
    where fences, crooked and straight, lean as they please.
    The broken bridge reveals the bright autumn water;
    tall trees call the evening crows back home.
    The old fisherman draws in his net and enters the reed-flowers,
    smiling and speaking of fish and shrimp.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The three rivers of Xiang (三湘, samhyeong) refer to the rivers of the Xiang region in ancient China, a region of profound poetic significance.
  - key: ''
    value: Hengyang (衡陽) is a historical location associated with the turning point of geese's migration southward, a classical poetic image.
  - key: ''
    value: The temple block (木魚, mok-eo in Korean) is a wooden instrument carved in the shape of a fish, struck to mark time during Buddhist ceremonies—here translated as such to preserve the original intent, though the Chinese text uses the character for whale.
  - key: ''
    value: Wang Wei (摩詰), the Tang dynasty painter-poet, is referenced as the ideal artist whose spiritual vision transcends mere representation.
